title.narrative: Government Debt and Infrastructure Finance - The Gambia. Government Debt & Infrastructure Finance - The Gambia. Government Debt and Infrastructure Finance - Gambia. Technical Assistance for Government Debt and Infrastructure Finance - The Gambia

description.narrative: Establish a stable and predictable macroeconomic environment that encourages the private sector to make productivity- and growth-enhancing investments. A solid macroeconomic foundation for growth consists of stable fiscal and monetary policies and institutions and the ability of the government to utilize such policies to productively influence the economy.

Support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy, most importantly financial intermediation – the efficient generation and allocation of savings to their most productive use.

This award strives to support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy. More specifically, this includes Project was canceled.. OTA intends to provide assistance to MOFEA to achieve the following objectives: Operationalization of the MOFEA’s debt strategy which might include extension of the government securities maturity profile through issuance of longer-dated T-Bonds; re-profiling of the T-Bill portfolio; predictable government securities auctions; organization of market intermediaries; and improvements in government securities placement and trading and settlement procedures and infrastructure; Implementation of an appropriate organizational structure and well-defined functionalities for government debt issuance and management within the MOFEA; Enhanced MOFEA frameworks and capacity for debt strategy development; borrowing planning; fiscal risk analysis and management; portfolio risk analysis and mitigation; contingent liabilities framework; and market communication.. Project is suspended. Project is closed. OTA intends to provide assistance to MOFEA to achieve the following objectives: Operationalization of the MOFEAs debt strategy which might include extension of the government securities maturity profile through issuance of longer-dated T-Bonds; re-profiling of the T-Bill portfolio; predictable government securities auctions; organization of market intermediaries; and improvements in government securities placement and trading and settlement procedures and infrastructure; Implementation of an appropriate organizational structure and well-defined functionalities for government debt issuance and management within the MOFEA; Enhanced MOFEA frameworks and capacity for debt strategy development; borrowing planning; fiscal risk analysis and management; portfolio risk analysis and mitigation; contingent liabilities framework; and market communication.. The Debt Resident Advisor will provide technical assistance to the Ministry of Finance and Economic Affairs’ (MOFEA) Department of Loans and Debt Management (DLDM) for debt management operations and local currency debt market development. Project objectives include the implementation of the Medium Term Debt Strategy and developing the Gambian domestic debt market.. Project is closed..
